            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/15849",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bkarwin",
                        "name": "bkarwin",
                        "displayName": "Bill Karwin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Assign to Bill Karwin.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bkarwin",
                        "name": "bkarwin",
                        "displayName": "Bill Karwin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-07-17T13:54:19.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-07-17T13:54:19.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/18065",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=kodmasin",
                        "name": "kodmasin",
                        "displayName": "Boris Tomi?",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "This is just small patch I made to fix this bug until something better is not created. It should be applied to Zend\/Db\/Statement\/Pdo.php file.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=kodmasin",
                        "name": "kodmasin",
                        "displayName": "Boris Tomi?",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-12-27T11:10:41.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-12-27T11:10:41.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/18111",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=kodmasin",
                        "name": "kodmasin",
                        "displayName": "Boris Tomi?",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Small patch I have attached here is not good because Exception constructor takes long type for code and SQLSTATE can contain uppercase letters. I think that Zend_Db_Exception should be changed to address this issue.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=kodmasin",
                        "name": "kodmasin",
                        "displayName": "Boris Tomi?",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-12-29T06:34:50.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-12-29T06:34:50.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/18120",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=kodmasin",
                        "name": "kodmasin",
                        "displayName": "Boris Tomi?",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "[^ZF-1731_patch.patch] . New patch I have created. It is changing Zend_Db_Exception and Zend_Db_Statement_Pdo. I hope that this patch is properly created as explained in Submitting a bug fix.\nI do not know will it be better to change Zend_Db_Statement_Exception. I thought that other Db exceptions could benefit from this patch so I changed Zend_Db_Exception instead.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=kodmasin",
                        "name": "kodmasin",
                        "displayName": "Boris Tomi?",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-12-30T13:03:50.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-12-30T13:03:50.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/19173",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "It is not necessary to change Zend_Db_Exception itself because standard Exception class from PHP already includes code property.\n\nThe problem of having an error-code is not a Zend_Db only problem. It is related to all ZF-classes.\nWe have already a proposal which is finished for review \nhttp:\/\/framework.zend.com\/wiki\/pages\/viewpage.action?pageId=22134\n\nThis will integrate error-codes consistently for ALL classes. I will therefor close this issue.\nTo help integration vote for the proposal.\n\nI think it will be integrated shortly after 1.5 is released.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-02-16T16:06:33.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-02-16T16:06:33.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/19174",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Duplicate for an already available proposal... closing this issue in benefit of the proposal.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-02-16T16:07:31.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-02-16T16:07:31.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/19175",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=kodmasin",
                        "name": "kodmasin",
                        "displayName": "Boris Tomi?",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "ZF-1768  was duplicate of this bug. As I understand this issue user needs to get SQLSTATE (SQL standard error codes). If I understanded http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/wiki\/pages\/viewpage.action?pageId=22134 \nproposal it will not give possibility to specify SQL errors.\n\nSo probably we should open new feature request to add something like getSQLErrorCode member function to Zend_Db_Exception.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=kodmasin",
                        "name": "kodmasin",
                        "displayName": "Boris Tomi?",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-02-16T16:26:38.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-02-16T16:26:38.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/19176",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Yes, I think this would be better.\nThere is also a problem which prevent this issue to be added: PDO errorcodes are not compatible with PHP exception codes.\n\nSo I think it would be better to have sqlError added as own property and method to Db exceptions.\nSeems better than use the standard errorcode, and in my opinion more secure ;-)",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-02-16T16:48:24.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-02-16T16:48:24.000+0000"
                }
            ]
        }
    },
